Webhook returned HTTP 200. Task complete. Here's what was built:
---
**body-map.js** (346 lines)
- SVG male body silhouette with 5 color-coded segments (right arm, left arm, trunk, right leg, left leg)
- Health rating algorithm — good=green, normal=blue, warning=amber, concern=red
- 3 view mode toggles: Muscle kg, Fat %, Fat kg
- Top stats bar: Weight, Body Fat %, Lean Mass %, BMI
- Color legend (4-tier health scale)
- Value pills overlaid on each SVG segment
- Segment detail cards below the silhouette with rating labels
- Fetches from `/api/health/measurements/latest` on activation
- Loading/empty/error states using the shared HealthAgent.ui helpers
**body-trends.js** (951 lines)
- 6 predefined charts + 1 custom metric chart
- Chart.js line charts with gradient fills, 0.35 tension, 800ms easeOutQuart animation
- Custom crosshair plugin (dashed vertical + horizontal guide lines on hover)
- Dark/light theme-aware colors — auto-refreshes on theme toggle
- Per-chart time range pills: 1W / 1M / 3M / 6M / 1Y / ALL
- Each chart has a fullscreen button (Escape to exit)
- Custom Metric chart with dropdown selector for all 24 measurement fields
- All data fetched from `/api/health/measurements/trends?metrics=...&limit=90`
- Charts: blue Weight, amber Body Fat %, green Muscle+Lean dual, purple stacked Body Comp, cyan Hydration dual-axis, pink BMI+Metabolic Age dual-axis, teal Custom
**Wired into the app shell:**
- `app.js` now calls `HealthAgent.bodyMap.init()` / `HealthAgent.bodyTrends.init()` on sub-tab activation
- `index.html` loads Chart.js CDN + both JS files
- `app.css` has ~240 lines of new CSS for stats bar, toggles, legend, SVG, segment cards, chart fullscreen, and responsive breakpoints
